snippet: Dell said its third-quarter profit was hurt by lower PC sales and weaker demand from large corporations.
abstract: Dell reports third-quarter net income of $475 million, or 27 cents a share, down sharply from $893 million, or 49 cents a share, in year-ago quarter; revenue fell 11 percent to $13.7 billion; company was hurt by lower PC sales and weaker corporate demand as it struggled to compete with Asian rivals.
lead_paragraph: Dell said its third-quarter profit was hurt by lower PC sales and weaker demand from large corporations.

headline.main: Hurt by Rivals From Asia, Dell Profit Falls 47%
headline.print_headline: Hurt by Rivals From Asia, Dell Profit Falls 47%
